		<p>^^ Actually Crystal, cats in European witchcraft or Old Religion were seen as &#8216;familiar spirits&#8217; or &#8216;spitit guides&#8217; of witches.  So when Christianity demonized witches, they naturally demonized cats as being harbingers of the devil.  I&#8217;m not certain, but in a way the large cats like leopards and lions can perhaps be thought of as familiar spirits of the goddess.</p>
<p>My question to Max is that could there be a possible connection between the goddesses of Southwest Asia riding on big cats and those of India?? I have been researching Hindu goddess worship and I have covered some striking parallels between these and those of the &#8216;Near East&#8217;, particularly Mesopotamia.</p>

