		<p>David, i believe that was part of Crystal&#8217;s point. As to India, many scholars have proposed a borrowing of lion-riding goddesses from western Asia. That may be, but there is an indigenous strand centered on tigers, which i think entered in to the image of Durga riding on a tiger (sometimes a lion) and also influenced Tibetan icons of dakinis and goddesses (or yidams) riding on tigers. There are some clear west Asian influences on ancient Indian art, such as the Hurrian goddess type who shows up in the carved ringstones of 1st millennium bce India.</p>

		<div class="reply">
